cs.NE, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.SI 

The paper discusses the application of Self Organizing Maps (SOM) in various modeling tasks, which are commonly associated with the sub-categories of Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE), Machine Learning (cs.LG), Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI), Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition (cs.CV), and Social and Information Networks (cs.SI). The paper also introduces a novel concept of contextual numbers, which can be used for high dimensional spatiotemporal dynamics, further supporting the likelihood of the above-mentioned sub-categories.
